e actually tried to investigate empirically the dilemmas that they, as practitioners, deal with every day. Often audience members interrupt our presentations to ask, "What would you do with a kid who . . ." and we are always eager to try to apply research to a new real-life situation. Sometimes, we find it difficult to answer, and then the audience member's question prompts a new empirical study! It is therefore a genuine pleasure to present this book, which covers those empirical studies, to readers who can then actually implement research-based accommodations decisions"--Preface. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2014 APA, all rights reserved).  aElectronic reproduction.bWashington, D.C. :cAmerican Psychological Association,d2014.nAvailable via World Wide Web.nAccess limited by licensing agreement.7s2014 dcunns  a21 44 57 0aTesting accommodationszUnited States. 0aStudents with disabilitiesxServices forzUnited States. 2aDisabled Children.1 aLewandowski, Lawrence J. 0aSchool psychology book series.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://ovidsp.ovid.com/ovidweb.cgi?T=JS&NEWS=N&PAGE=toc&SEARCH=2014-16766.dd&LINKTYPE=asBody&D=psbk403MacEwan University Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/direct.asp?db=pzh&jid=%22201416766%22&scope=site403Concordia University of Edmonton Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=pzh&jid=201416766&site=ehost-live  hUAINzPSYCBOOKS  hUAINmCONCORDIAzPSYCBKSCON  hUAINmGR_MAC_INTzPSYCBKSGM  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6700443-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu9/30/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBOOKS  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6700443-2001lINTERNETmCONCORDIArYsYtE-RESOURCEu9/30/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSCON  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6700443-3001lINTERNETmGR_MAC_INTrYsYtE-RESOURCEu9/30/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSGM01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no90022654bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/51249602